    • Field Detail

      • MAX_PERCENTILE

        public static double MAX_PERCENTILE
        The highest percentile to use when attempting to calculate a value. Tests with the BMI growth charts for females at 240 months show that values greater than 0.99739 cause a term in the equation to go negative causing the code to return NaN. Values slightly less than that can return unrealistic values. This provides a limit to the maximum percentile that will be looked up.
